Sherlock Holmes.

73
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:31,920
Sherlock Holmes.

74
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,600
- Sebastian. - Hiya, buddy. how long - eight years

75
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,560
since I last clapped eyes on you?

76
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:38,670
This is my friend, John Watson.

77
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:40,160
- Friend? - Colleague.

78
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,280
Right.

79
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,920
Grab a pew.

80
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,720
Do you need anything, coffee, water?

81
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:51,600
No. We're all sorted here, thanks.

82
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:55,120
So you're doing well. You've been abroad a lot.

83
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,760
Well, so?

84
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,200
Flying all the way around the world twice in a month.

85
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:03,480
Right. You're doing that thing.

86
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,190
We were at uni together,

87
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:07,280
and this guy here had a trick he used to do.

88
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,800
It's not a trick.

89
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,840
He could look at you and tell you your whole life story.

90
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,170
Yes, I've seen him do it.

91
00:08:12,170 --> 00:08:14,280
Put the wind up everybody, we hated him.

92
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:16,400
We'd come down to breakfast in the formal hall

93
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,440
and this freak would know you'd been shagging the previous night.

94
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,530
I simply observed.

95
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:20,900
Go on, enlighten me.

96
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:24,140
Two trips a month, flying all the way around the world,

97
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:24,600
you're quite right.

98
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,940
How could you tell?

99
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:28,120
Are you going to tell me there's a stain on my tie

100
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,600
from some special kind of ketchup you can only buy in Manhattan?

101
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:33,080
- No, I... - Is it the mud on my shoes?

102
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:37,080
I was just chatting with your secretary outside.

103
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,640
She told me.

104
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:47,600
I'm glad you could make it over, we've had a break-in.

105
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,640
Sir William's office -   the bank's former chairman.

106
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:53,520
The room's been left here like a sort of memorial.

107
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,600
Someone broke in late last night.

108
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,160
- What did they steal? - Nothing.

109
00:08:58,160 --> 00:09:00,640
Just left a little message.

110
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,000
60 seconds apart.

111
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:28,920
So, someone came up here in the middle of the night,

112
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,520
splashed paint around and left within a minute.

113
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,320
How many ways into that office?

114
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,480
Well, that's where this gets really interesting.

115
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:39,320
Every door that opens in this bank, it gets locked right here.

116
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,280
Every walk-in cupboard, every toilet.

117
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,760
That door didn't open last night?

118
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,760
There's a hole in our security.

119
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,400
Find it and we'll pay you -

120
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,000
five figures.

121
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,760
This is an advance.

122
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,400
Tell me how he got in.

123
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,920
There's a bigger one on its way.

124
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:57,120
I don't need an incentive, Sebastian.

125
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:02,680
He's, er..he's kidding you, obviously.

126
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,440
Shall I look after that for him?

127
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,920
Thanks.

128
