01:20:01,780 --> 01:20:04,850
Resourceful? Dynamic? Enigmatic?

1064
01:20:04,850 --> 01:20:05,660
Late?

1065
01:20:05,660 --> 01:20:07,220
That's a semi-automatic. If you fire it,

1066
01:20:07,220 --> 01:20:10,060
the bullet will travel at over 1,000 metres per second.

1067
01:20:10,060 --> 01:20:11,580
Well?

1068
01:20:11,580 --> 01:20:13,940
Well...

1069
01:20:13,940 --> 01:20:16,140
..the radius curvature of these walls is nearly four metres.

1070
01:20:16,140 --> 01:20:17,420
If you miss, the bullet will ricochet.

1071
01:20:17,420 --> 01:20:19,100
Could hit anyone.

1072
01:20:19,100 --> 01:20:22,020
Might even bounce off the tunnel and hit you.

1073
01:21:42,340 --> 01:21:43,660
It's all right.

1074
01:21:45,820 --> 01:21:48,140
You're going to be all right. It's over now.

1075
01:21:54,260 --> 01:21:56,740
Don't worry.

1076
01:21:56,740 --> 01:21:58,780
Next date won't be like this.

1077
01:22:12,820 --> 01:22:15,220
We'll just slip off. No need to mention us in your report.

1078
01:22:15,220 --> 01:22:16,550
Mr Holmes...

1079
01:22:16,550 --> 01:22:18,340
I have high hopes for you, Inspector.

1080
01:22:18,340 --> 01:22:20,660
A glittering career.

1081
01:22:20,660 --> 01:22:22,700
I go where you point me.

1082
01:22:24,740 --> 01:22:26,220
Exactly.

1083
01:22:35,420 --> 01:22:37,180
So, nine million.

1084
01:22:37,180 --> 01:22:38,070
- Million. - Yes

1085
01:22:38,070 --> 01:22:42,540
Nine million for Jade pin dragon den black tramway.

1086
01:22:42,540 --> 01:22:45,020
An instruction to all their London operatives.

1087
01:22:45,020 --> 01:22:47,700
A message. What they were trying to reclaim.

1088
01:22:47,700 --> 01:22:49,540
- What, a jade pin? - Worth 9 million pounds.

1089
01:22:49,540 --> 01:22:50,700
Bring it to the Tramway,

1090
01:22:50,700 --> 01:22:51,860
their London hideout.

1091
01:22:51,860 --> 01:22:54,460
Hang on. A hairpin worth 9 million pounds?

1092
01:22:54,460 --> 01:22:56,700
- Apparently. - Why so much?

1093
01:22:56,700 --> 01:22:58,860
Depends who owned it.

1094
01:23:04,500 --> 01:23:06,820
Two operatives based in London.

1095
01:23:06,820 --> 01:23:09,700
They travel over to Dalian to smuggle those vases.

1096
01:23:09,700 --> 01:23:13,060
One of them helps himself to something, a little hairpin.

1097
01:23:13,060 --> 01:23:15,540
- Worth 9 million. - Eddie Van Coon was the thief,

1098
01:23:15,540 --> 01:23:17,540
he stole the treasure when he was in China.

1099
01:23:17,540 --> 01:23:19,220
How do you know it was Van Coon, not Lukis?

1100
01:23:19,220 --> 01:23:22,300
- Even the killer didn't know that. - Because of the soap.

1101
01:23:34,260 --> 01:23:36,820
- Amanda?   - He brought you a present.

1102
01:23:36,820 --> 01:23:38,300
Oh, hello.

1103
01:23:38,300 --> 01:23:40,980
A little gift when he came back from China.

1104
01:23:40,980 --> 01:23:42,380
How do you know that?

1105
01:23:42,380 --> 01:23:45,380
You weren't just his PA, were you?

1106
01:23:45,380 --> 01:23:46,980
Someone's been gossiping.

1107
01:23:46,980 --> 01:23:48,820
- No. - Then I don't understand why...

1108
01:23:48,820 --> 01:23:50,780
Scented hand soap in his apartment.

1109
01:23:50,780 --> 01:23:54,220
300ml of it. Bottle almost finished.

1110
01:23:54,220 --> 01:23:55,220
Sorry...?

1111
01:23:55,220 --> 01:23:59,220
I don't think Eddie Van Coon was the type of chap to buy himself hand soap,

1112
01:23:59,220 --> 01:24:01,340
not unless he had a lady coming over.

1113
01:24:01,340 --> 01:24:03,940
And it's the same brand as that hand cream there on your desk.

1114
01:24:06,060 --> 01:24:09,580
Look, it wasn't serious between us.

1115
01:24:09,580 --> 01:24:12,720
It was over in a flash, it couldn't last.

1116
01:24:12,720 --> 01:24:14,180
He was my boss.

1117
01:24:14,180 --> 01:24:16,780
What happened? Why did you end it?

1118
01:24:19,020 --> 01:24:21,780
I thought he didn't appreciate me.

1119
01:24:21,780 --> 01:24:23,580
Took me for granted.

1120
01:24:25,140 --> 01:24:26,900
Stood me up once too often.

1121
01:24:26,900 --> 01:24:29,490
We'd plan to go away for the weekend,

1122
01:24:29,490 --> 01:24:30,700
and then he'd just leave.

1123
01:24:30,700 --> 01:24:33,460
Fly off to China at a moment's notice.

1124
01:24:33,460 --> 01:24:35,700
And he brought you a present from abroad to say sorry.

1125
01:24:37,140 --> 01:24:40,420
Can I just have a look at it?

1126
01:24:46,340 --> 01:24:49,380
He really climbed up onto the balcony?

1127
01:24:49,380 --> 01:24:51,220
Nail a plank across the window

1128
01:24:51,220 --> 01:24:52,460
and all your problems are over.

1129
01:24:54,780 --> 01:24:56,380
Thanks.

1130
01:24:56,380 --> 01:24:59,820
He said he bought it in a street market.

1131
01:24:59,820 --> 01:25:02,740
Oh, I don't think that's true. I think he pinched it.

1132
01:25:02,740 --> 01:25:04,260
Yeah, that's Eddie.

1133
01:25:04,260 --> 01:25:06,700
Didn't know its value, just thought it would suit you.

1134
01:25:06,700 --> 01:25:09,620
Oh? What's it worth?

1135
01:25:11,180 --> 01:25:13,820
9 million pounds.

1136
01:25:16,820 --> 01:25:18,060
Oh, my God.

1137
01:25:18,060 --> 01:25:19,620
Oh, my God!

1138
01:25:22,380 --> 01:25:23,740
Nine million?!

1139
01:25:36,460 --> 01:25:40,580
Over 1,000 years old and it's sitting on her bedside table every night.

1140
01:25:40,580 --> 01:25:41,860
He didn't know its value.

1141
01:25:41,860 --> 01:25:43,620
Didn't know why they were chasing him.

1142
01:25:45,180 --> 01:25:47,860
Should we just got her a lucky cat.

1143
01:25:51,140 --> 01:25:54,260
- You mind, don't you? - What?

1144
01:25:54,260 --> 01:25:57,220
That she escaped. General Shan.

1145
01:25:57,220 --> 01:25:59,180
It's not enough that we got her two henchmen.

1146
01:25:59,180 --> 01:26:00,980
Must be a vast network, John.

1147
01:26:00,980 --> 01:26:02,740
Thousands of operatives.

1148
01:26:02,740 --> 01:26:05,260
You and I, we barely scratched the surface.

1149
01:26:05,260 --> 01:26:07,380
You cracked the code though, Sherlock.

1150
01:26:07,380 --> 01:26:10,220
And maybe Dimmock can track down all of them now he knows it.

1151
01:26:10,220 --> 01:26:14,660
No. No, I crack this code,

1152
01:26:14,660 --> 01:26:18,740
all the smugglers have to do is pick up another book.

1153
01:26:44,060 --> 01:26:46,820
Without you...

1154
01:26:46,820 --> 01:26:49,820
without your assistance,

1155
01:26:49,820 --> 01:26:53,100
we would not have found passage into London.

1156
01:26:56,540 --> 01:26:58,540
You have my thanks.

1157
01:27:02,620 --> 01:27:17,140


1158
01:27:03,860 --> 01:27:17,140


1159
01:27:09,500 --> 01:27:11,380
We did not anticipate...

1160
01:27:13,100 --> 01:27:15,980
We did not know this man would come.

1161
01:27:18,060 --> 01:27:20,500
This Sherlock Holmes.

1162
01:27:23,900 --> 01:27:27,580
And now your safety is compromised.

1163
01:27:29,780 --> 01:27:36,780


1164
01:27:37,340 --> 01:27:39,980
I will not reveal your identity.

1165
